This paper discusses the evaluation of deep learning architectures, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of best single model performance is a common practice in deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the evaluation of computer vision models, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for correcting the flaws in the current practice, which involves the use of expected performance, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of language models, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category.
